        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses the possible explanation of why fly-orchid plants in a correspondent’s garden had no pollen-masses removed while <hi rend="italic">Orchis maculata</hi> had all of its pollen-masses removed. CD points out that different orchids are fertilised by different insects. The insects needed to fertilise the fly-orchid may not have inhabited the site of the correspondent’s garden.</p> 
        </abstract>
